From 740b40276c6dd22f5594458dd5a8fdbcdc2d9146 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Wed, 24 Dec 2025 12:13:37 +1100
Subject: [PATCH 60/73] arm64: dts: cix: sky1: Add cache topology, fix DTS
 warnings, enable USB3 LPM

Add CPU cache topology for Sky1 SoC:
- CPU0-3 (A520): 32KB L1I, 32KB L1D, direct to L3
- CPU4-11 (A720): 64KB L1I, 64KB L1D, 512KB L2, then L3
- Shared 12MB L3 cache in DSU

This fixes "Unable to detect cache hierarchy for CPU 0" warning.

Fix DTS compilation warnings:
- Remove leading zeros from unit addresses (iommu, ddr_ctrl, its, rng)
- Remove leading "0x" from unit addresses (smmu-mmhub nodes)
- Rename xspi node to spi per SPI bus binding requirements
- Add #address-cells/#size-cells to DP port nodes (sky1-orion-o6.dts)
- Fix SPI child node names to use chip-select as unit address

Enable USB3 Link Power Management:
- Add usb3-lpm-capable property to all 6 USB SuperSpeed controllers
- Enables U1/U2 low-power states for USB3 devices
